    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#gpc1961"/>, p. 44, n. <citedRange>24</citedRange>, fig. 40 p. 45 (from †Oliverio's papers)</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>20.754, b</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>066200</citedRange></bibl>.
                Cf; <bibl><ptr target="#sillani2014"/>, p. <citedRange>104</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Zeus"><name nymRef="#Ζεύς"><expan><abbr>Ζη</abbr><ex>νός</ex></expan></name></persName>,
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων">Ἀπόλ<lb n="3" break="no"/>λων</name></persName>.
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="1">
                        <rdg resp="#gpc1961"><expan><abbr>Ζή</abbr><ex>ν</ex></expan></rdg>
                        <rdg resp="#gpc1961"><expan><abbr>Ζη</abbr><ex>νός</ex></expan></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Autel</supplied> de Zeus. Apollon.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altar</supplied> of Zeus. Apollo.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
                <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altare</supplied> di Zeus. Apollo.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>About the circumstances of the discovery and the trip from Cyrene to Massah directed by Ghislanzoni in 1918 with participation of Oliverio, see Ghislanzoni archive described by <bibl><ptr target="#sillani2014"/>, p. <citedRange>104</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
                <p>The dubious nominative <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ζήν</foreign> for the name of Zeus being not attested up to now in Cyrenaica, we prefer to read the abbreviated genitive,
                    although the nieghbouring namle of Apollo is at the nominative.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
